# Precomputed artifacts are regeneratable from candidates.jsonl via
# `python -m src.precompute` -- not checked in. This is deliberate, not
# just "keep the repo lean": artifacts are built from a specific
# candidates.jsonl, and rank.py validates a hash of that file against what
# the cached artifacts were built from (see ensure_artifacts() in rank.py).
# Shipping artifacts built from a different candidates file than whatever
# Redrob's Stage 3 sandbox actually provides would be actively wrong, not
# just stale -- so precompute always runs fresh against the real input file.
artifacts/*.npz
artifacts/*.parquet
artifacts/*.pkl
artifacts/candidate_order.csv
artifacts/*.meta.json

# Raw data (not ours to redistribute / too large for git) -- but small
# sample fixtures used for sandbox/local testing ARE checked in (see
# data/sample_candidates_*.jsonl)
data/candidates.jsonl
candidates.jsonl

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/

# OS
.DS_Store

# Scratch
notebooks/explore*.py.bak
